    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-13T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-13T13:00:00-05:00" n="755"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/11–1348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Special Representative of the United States in Israel</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McDonald</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-13T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 13, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>216. Dept had received several reports indicating number Amer citizens and
                    aircraft of Amer and Panamanian registry involved in movement fighter aircraft
                    and arms from Czecho to Israel in violation <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>
                    resolutions May 29 and July 15 and contravention US Govt Policy on arms
                    shipments to Near East. (Urtel 243 Nov 8.<note n="1" xml:id="d755fn1">Not
                        printed.</note>) Planes overflying Austria refused respond international
                    signals to land given by US Air Forces. Rather than accede Air Force request for
                    authorization to shoot down planes Dept on basis affidavits from Amer citizens
                    involved instructed Emb Praha end July request assistance Czech Govt in stopping
                    use Czech airfields by Amer aircraft using Amer crews and bearing Amer markings
                    and engaged in clandestine operations. Czech Govt also requested assist Emb take
                    up passports personnel such crews. Foregoing action believed in accord <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> resolutions May 29 and July 15 as well as US Govt
                    Policy on this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
